column5:
I was recently feeling very tired and run down, and I started to experience some shortness of breath. I went to see my doctor, who ran some tests and determined that I had anemia. Anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells carry oxygen to the body's tissues, so when you have anemia, you can feel tired and short of breath.

My doctor prescribed me some medication to treat my anemia, and I also started taking iron supplements
